1. Title:- Understanding Classes,Objects and Constructors
2. Practical Number:- 5 
3. Date:- 2025.03.28
4. Time:- 10.30 a.m to 12.30 p.m

5. Objective:- Create a Paper Class
               Create a Document Class
               Create new Document object and Add Paper Object inside that document 

6. Theory/Concepts:- 
              -How to Create Classes
              -How to Create Objects

7. Algorithm / Flowchart :
                    step1: START
                    step2: Define Class Paper
                                -Declare integer variables: length, width
                                -Declare a string variable: text
                    step3: Define Class Document
                                -Declare a string variable: name
                                -Declare a variable p of type Paper
                    step4: In the main() Method
                                -Create a Document object d
                                -Set the name of d
                                -Create a Paper object and assign it to d.p
                                -Set properties of Paper object p
                                    > Assign: length = 5
                                    > Assign: width = 2
                                    > Assign: text = "My Second Document"
                    step5: Print paper details
                    step6: END

8. Source Code
         //Exercise.java
                class Paper{
	
              	int length=5;
              	int width=2;
              	String text;
              	
              	//int length;
              	//int width;
              	
              }
              
              class Document
              {
              	String name;
              	Paper p;
	
            	public static void main(String[] args){
            		Document d=new Document();
            		System.out.println("Created a Document Object d");
            		d.name="My First Document";
            		System.out.println("Name of the Document d is "+d.name);
            
            		d.p=new Paper();
            		System.out.println("Size l*w of the paper of the Document d is "+d.p.length+" * "+d.p.width);
            		
            		Document d2=new Document();
            		System.out.println("Created a Document Object d2");
            		d2.name="My Second Document";
            		System.out.println("Name of the Document d is "+d2.name);
		
            	}		
            }

9. Expected Output:- 
              C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\2022 ICT 122 Day 5\Question 1>javac Exercise.java

              C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\2022 ICT 122 Day 5\Question 1>java Document
              Created a Document Object d
              Name of the Document d is My First Document
              Size l*w of the paper of the Document d is 5 * 2
              Created a Document Object d2
              Name of the Document d is My Second Document

10. Observations:- 
      -We Can Create a Object of Paper Inside Document Class
              d.p=new Paper();

      -We Can Assign Value to the Object Variables
              d.p.length = 5;
              d.p.width = 2;
              d.p.text= "My Second Document";


11. Conclusion:-  In Java We Can Create Classes And Object Using Those Classes Classes Can Be Seen As Building Blocks That Help Create Objects
